description: A Brazilian court ordered the removal of Adele's "Million Years Ago" from global platforms due to alleged plagiarism of Brazilian composer Toninho Geraes's song. Geraes claims the 2015 hit resembles his samba classic "Mulheres." Record labels Sony and Universal face fines for non-compliance. Geraes seeks royalties, damages, and songwriting credit.
title: Brazilian court orders Adele’s 2015 song 'Million Years Ago' removed over plagiarism
Retrospective 5% GST likely on food app delivery charge

description: Bangladesh's High Court reinstated the non-party caretaker government system for elections and the provision for constitutional amendment referendums.  The court deemed the abolition of the caretaker system unconstitutional.  While validating the current Yunus-led interim government, it clarified its distinct formation under Article 106, following presidential consultation with the Supreme Court.
title: Bangladesh HC restores caretaker govt system & referendum provision

description: Eleven Indians, primarily from Punjab, tragically died from carbon monoxide poisoning at a Georgia restaurant.  Families are devastated and struggling to repatriate the bodies for last rites.  Many victims had moved abroad seeking better lives, leaving behind grieving families and uncertain futures.
title: Georgia tragedy shatters Punjab families

description: Over 20 BJP MPs, including Union ministers, skipped the introduction of the 'one nation, one election' bills in Lok Sabha, despite a party whip. While some absences were explained by official events with PM Modi, others cited personal reasons.
title: Gadkari, Scindia among MPs playing truant despite LS whip

description: In a brazen attack, Lt. Gen. Igor Kirillov, head of Russia's chemical weapons protection, was assassinated in Moscow. Ukraine's SBU claims responsibility, calling him a war criminal responsible for chemical attacks. This marks the most significant killing of a Russian military official within Russia since the war began. Russia vows revenge while investigations are underway.
title: Kirillov highest-profile military official killed inside Russia since war

description: The Central government introduced bills in Lok Sabha for simultaneous elections, facing opposition uproar.  Critics argued it undermines federalism, while the government defended it as a long-standing recommendation.  The bills were referred to a joint parliamentary committee for scrutiny, highlighting the significant challenge of achieving the two-thirds majority required for constitutional amendments.
title: Govt introduces ONOE bills in LS; oppn says numbers won't add up to pass them

description: FM Nirmala Sitharaman informed LS that ED has restituted Rs 22,280 crore worth of assets to the victims of various scams, including return of over Rs 14,000 crore to various banks from the sale of assets of fugitive Vijay Mallya and Rs 1,053 crore of Nirav Modi.
title: Rs 14,000 crore returned to banks from Mallya assets sales: FM Nirmala

description: Elon Musk expressed interest in cricket after Google CEO Sundar Pichai tweeted about the India-Australia test match.  Pichai praised Jasprit Bumrah's performance, prompting a "Nice" from Musk and an invitation to watch a South Africa-India game together.  Bumrah's batting heroics, including a crucial 39-run stand, drew praise from fans and Google India.
title: When Jasprit Bumrah got Google CEO Sundar Pichai and Elon Musk talking cricket

description: The Supreme Court collegium reprimanded Allahabad High Court Justice Shekhar Kumar Yadav for his controversial speech at a VHP event.  The collegium advised him to maintain judicial dignity and exercise caution in public speeches, particularly regarding remarks about the Muslim community and the Uniform Civil Code, following complaints from lawyers and politicians.
title: SC collegium pulls up HC judge for VHP event speech

description: The National Testing Agency (NTA) will focus solely on administering entrance exams for higher education institutions starting next year, discontinuing recruitment tests.  Discussions are underway to determine whether NEET-UG will be conducted online or offline.  The NTA aims to implement recommendations for secure exam practices and ensure error-free testing.
title: NTA will hold only entrance exams, not job tests: Dharmendra Pradhan

description: In Nagpur, Uddhav Thackeray questioned the BJP's inaction on awarding Bharat Ratna to Veer Savarkar.  He urged a focus on development issues over historical debates.  Thackeray congratulated CM Fadnavis on the election win and held a closed-door meeting, sparking speculation about the opposition leader's post.  Both leaders expressed a desire for cultured political discourse in Maharashtra.
title: Uddhav calls on Fadnavis, seeks Bharat Ratna for Veer Savarkar

description: Following the discovery of a purported ancient temple in Sambhal, Muslim residents began demolishing homes built on allegedly encroached temple land.  Authorities initiated anti-encroachment and anti-power theft drives, particularly in minority-dominated areas, after a mosque survey sparked violence.  A sealed well near the mosque is now under excavation, adding to the ongoing investigation and restoration efforts surrounding the temple's rediscovery.
title: Muslim residents raze own homes near Sambhal’s ‘ancient’ temple

description: Yi Fei Chen, a Taiwanese artist, invented a unique tear gun.  The gun freezes tears into ice bullets. Chen built the gun after an argument with her professor.  The tear gun uses carbon dioxide to freeze the tears in 20 seconds. A spring mechanism launches the frozen tears.  The tear gun is still being perfected. Netizens praised Chen's creativity.
title: Taiwanese artist creates a gun that transforms her tears into 'ice bullets'

description: A BBC documentary, "Children of the Bombs," exposes the devastating impact of crude bombs in West Bengal politics. Since 1996, at least 565 children have been killed or injured, often mistaking bombs for toys. The film features heartbreaking accounts from survivors like Puchi and Poulami, who lost limbs in explosions.
title: ‘565 children injured or killed by bombs used by activists in Bengal since 1996’

description: Oman halted new import permits for Indian table eggs, impacting Namakkal's poultry industry.  This follows Qatar's recent weight restrictions, stranding a large egg shipment.  Exports to Oman, previously accounting for 50% of India's egg exports, have drastically declined since June, causing hardship for Indian exporters.
title: Oman stops eggs import, hits Tamil Nadu poultry industry

description: Tom Cruise, renowned for his iconic role in Top Gun, received the U.S. Navy's highest civilian honor for his significant contributions to the Navy and Marine Corps through his films. The award was presented at Longcross Studios near London. Cruise expressed pride in the recognition and praised the service of military personnel.
title: Tom Cruise honoured with US Navy's top civilian award; actor reacts

description: PayPal co-founder Peter Thiel argues that Silicon Valley's experiment with remote work revealed widespread unproductivity, leading to mass layoffs. He claims many remote workers weren't actually working, and companies ultimately dismissed them with little impact on operations.
title: Paypal founder: Silicon Valley called staff back to office as they realised that ...

description: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle's 2024 holiday card featuring their children, Archie and Lilibet, sparked controversy online.  Social media users questioned the photo's authenticity, citing inconsistencies in shadows, outlines, and the children's appearance, suggesting digital manipulation.
title: Digitally altered? Prince Harry, Markle's holiday card sparks speculation

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah's Rajya Sabha address on the Constitution's 75th anniversary sparked a strong reaction from Congress. They labeled his speech as "full of lies," accusing him of praising PM Modi and attacking Congress. Party leaders Kharge, Ramesh, and Singh challenged Shah's claims, citing inaccuracies regarding Ambedkar's statue, Nehru's policies, and the situation in J&K.
title: 'Bundle of lies': Congress slams Amit Shah over his remarks in RS
Numbers game: Why it could be a tough road ahead for 'One Nation, One Election'

description: Giannis Antetokounmpo's status for the Emirates NBA Cup final against the Oklahoma City Thunder is a game-time decision due to injury.  His dominant performance in the semi-final, including 32 points and 14 rebounds, highlights his importance to the Bucks. While other key players are also listed with injury concerns, Giannis's potential presence looms large over the game's outcome.
title: Will Giannis Antetokounmpo play tonight against the Oklahoma City Thunder?

description: Farmer leader Jagjit Singh Dallewal refused to meet with the Supreme Court-appointed committee, citing his health and the condition of injured farmers.  He insisted on negotiating only with the central government and criticized the committee's inaction in addressing their demands, including MSP guarantee and debt waiver.
title: No breakthrough: Protesting farmers refuse to meet panel set up by SC

description: Anupam Mittal, while promoting Shark Tank India's new season, seemingly aimed a playful jab at former judge Ashneer Grover. Referencing an old photo with Grover, Mittal remarked, 'May their soul rest in peace,' about absent sharks. He also reminisced about their appearance on Kaun Banega Crorepati with Amitabh Bachchan, calling it a 'dream come true.
title: Shark Tank India 4: Anupam Mittal takes a sly jibe at Ashneer Grover

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister M.K. Stalin felicitated 18-year-old D. Gukesh, the world's youngest chess champion, with ₹5 crore and announced the establishment of a chess academy. Stalin praised Gukesh's achievement, calling him an inspiration for aspiring youth. Gukesh expressed gratitude for the government's support and acknowledged Viswanathan Anand as his role model.
title: Rs 5 crore award for Gukesh! Tamil Nadu CM felicitates

description: Chet Holmgren will miss the Emirates NBA Cup final due to a hip injury. Despite his absence, the Oklahoma City Thunder boasts a 20-5 record, making them the top team in the Western Conference.  Holmgren's impressive pre-injury performance and positive attitude during recovery are highlighted.  His return is anticipated in January 2025.
title: Will Chet Holmgren play tonight against the Milwaukee Bucks?
'Effort to create one market': Farmers on One Nation One Election

description: Priyanka Gandhi Vadra criticised Uttar Pradesh chief minister Yogi Adityanath's remarks about her carrying a "Palestine" bag in Parliament. Adityanath highlighted UP youths working in Israel for high salaries, while Vadra countered that sending youth to a war zone for employment is shameful, citing their precarious situation amidst conflict and exploitation by companies.
title: 'Matter of shame': Priyanka slams UP CM for 'sending youths to war zone Israel'
LK Advani's condition 'stable', expected to be shifted from ICU soon

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah criticized Congress for amending the Constitution to maintain power, treating it as their "private fiefdom." He accused them of being anti-reservation, citing their handling of the Kaka Saheb Kalelkar Commission report. Shah also pointed to Congress's inconsistent stance on EVMs and alleged that they neglected Muslim women's rights for political gain.
title: Shah ends Constitution debate with fiery attack on Gandhi family

description: LeBron James, despite a recent foot injury, led the Lakers to a 116-110 victory over the Grizzlies, snapping their losing streak.  Lakers coach JJ Redick praised James's performance and leadership, highlighting his dedication and attention to detail even at 40 years old. Redick emphasized James's crucial role in the team's success.
title: Los Angeles Lakers coach lauds NBA star LeBron James after ceremonious comeback

description: World-renowned tabla maestro Zakir Hussain, 73, passed away in San Francisco due to complications from pulmonary fibrosis. His family confirmed the news, prompting tributes from figures like Sachin Tendulkar, who recalled Hussain's humility and musical genius. Hussain, son of Ustad Alla Rakha, collaborated with both Indian and Western music icons, leaving a vast legacy.
title: Tendulkar's viral video of tabla masterclass with late Zakir Hussain

description: Hardik Pandya will miss the initial Vijay Hazare Trophy matches due to personal commitments but plans to join the Baroda team, led by his brother Krunal, later in the tournament. Hardik had a strong Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy performance with both bat and ball. Baroda reached the SMAT semi-finals, losing to eventual champions Mumbai despite Krunal's contribution.
title: Pandya to miss first few games of Vijay Hazare Trophy

description: During the Brisbane Test's fourth day, Sunil Gavaskar criticized Mohammed Siraj's risky single with Ravindra Jadeja, nearly causing a run-out. Gavaskar questioned Siraj's cricketing awareness as a number nine batsman. Despite this, Jasprit Bumrah and Akash Deep forged a crucial last-wicket stand, helping India avoid the follow-on.
title: 'You are a No. 9 batter': Gavaskar slams Siraj for risky move

description: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath criticized Priyanka Gandhi for carrying a bag with "Palestine" written on it, highlighting that his government has sent over 5,000 youth to Israel for jobs with a monthly salary of Rs 1.5 lakh.  The BJP labeled Gandhi's bag a symbol of appeasement, while she continues to advocate for peace in the ongoing Israel-Palestine conflict.
title: 'While Cong holds bag, UP sending youth to Israel: Yogi's dig at Priyanka

description: Star Indian pacer  Jasprit Bumrah's batting prowess was on display again as he helped India avoid the follow-on against Australia at the Gabba on Tuesday. His unbeaten 39-run partnership for the 10th wicket came a day after he reminded a reporter of his record 35 runs in a single Test over against Stuart Broad.
title: Google's witty reply to Bumrah’s 'search it' remark
Why Iran is not imposing its new stricter hijab law

description: Australian pacer Josh Hazlewood's Border-Gavaskar Trophy campaign ended prematurely due to a right calf strain sustained during the Gabba Test. Hazlewood, recently returned from a side strain, bowled only one over before leaving the field. His absence is a significant blow to Australia's bowling attack. Scott Boland is expected to replace him for the remaining matches in Melbourne and Sydney.
title: 'Show a bit of care and love for Josh Hazlewood': Nathon Lyon

description: Rain threatens to wash out the final day of the gripping Gabba Test between India and Australia.  With a 90% chance of rain and a flood alert issued, a draw appears likely. India, still trailing by 193 runs, showed resilience on Day 4, avoiding the follow-on thanks to crucial knocks from KL Rahul and Ravindra Jadeja.
title: Rain set to play spoilsport on Day 5 at Gabba

description: NFL star Travis Kelce spared no expense for Taylor Swift's 35th birthday. He showered her with $175,000 worth of gifts. These included a Rolex and Van Cleef & Arpels jewelry. Kelce hired a private chef and bartender for an intimate celebration. The couple enjoyed the special day away from the public eye.
title: Taylor Swift’s 35th birthday celebration included pvt chef and $175,000 in gifts

description: NEET UG 2025 Syllabus Announced: The National Medical Commission (NMC) released the NEET UG 2025 syllabus, covering Physics, Chemistry, and Biology.  The Undergraduate Medical Education Board urges stakeholders to refer to the updated syllabus on the NMC website for study material preparation and exam readiness for the 2025-2026 academic session. The detailed syllabus includes units and topics for each subject.
title: NEET UG 2025 Syllabus announced, check subject-wise topics

description: Team India staged a valiant fightback on Day 4 of the Brisbane Test, averting an innings defeat against Australia. KL Rahul and Ravindra Jadeja's half-centuries, combined with a crucial partnership between Jasprit Bumrah and Akash Deep, propelled India to 252/9.
title: Google India joins Indian cricket fans to say: I only believe in Jassi Bhai

description: Allahabad High Court Judge Shekhar Kumar Yadav appeared before the Supreme Court collegium to address his controversial remarks on the Uniform Civil Code (UCC). Justice Yadav had advocated for the UCC as a means to eliminate unequal legal systems, sparking debate and prompting the Supreme Court's intervention.
title: Controversial remarks: Allahabad HC judge appears before SC collegium

description: Chhagan Bhujbal, a leader of the Ajit Pawar faction of the NCP, expressed his discontent at being excluded from the recent Maharashtra cabinet expansion.  He revealed that he declined a Rajya Sabha seat offered after his Lok Sabha aspirations were disregarded. Bhujbal questioned his treatment within the party and hinted at Chief Minister Devendra Fadnavis's support for his inclusion.
title: 'Am I a toy?':NCP's Bhujbal on exclusion from Maha cabinet expansion

description: A 13-year-old girl suffered a severe scalp injury on a swing at a Tikamgarh fair when her hair got entangled. She was transported to Jhansi for surgery after initial treatment at the district hospital. The swing operator also sustained a fractured leg trying to halt the ride.
title: Girl's scalp ripped off as hair gets entangled in a swing at MP mela

description: Sameer Wankhede refused to discuss Shah Rukh Khan in a recent interview.  Ranveer Singh reacted sweetly to paparazzi inquiries about his daughter, Dua. Mahira Khan opened up about the emotional toll of her viral photos with Ranbir Kapoor.  Shatrughan Sinha defended Sonakshi Sinha against Mukesh Khanna's comments. Adnan Sami mourned the loss of Zakir Hussain.
title: Wankhede skips question on Shah Rukh, Mahira on smoking photos with Ranbir: Top 5 news

description: India's aviation ministry has introduced new rules to combat hoax threats against flights. Individuals making such threats now face fines of up to ₹1 lakh, along with other criminal charges. The Bureau of Civil Aviation Security (BCAS) has also been granted authority to deny boarding or remove individuals from aircraft for security reasons.
title: Aviation ministry takes big steps to curb hoax threats

description: The BJP plans to send notices to about 20 MPs who missed the 'one nation, one election' bill vote. The bill seeks to hold simultaneous Lok Sabha and Assembly elections. It failed to get the needed two-thirds majority. Opposition parties opposed the bill. The government said the bill aligns with the Constitution.
title: BJP to issue notice to 20 MPs skipping voting on ONOE: Report

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister M.K. Stalin will honor newly crowned World Chess Champion D. Gukesh with a ₹5 crore cheque on Tuesday. Gukesh, 18, returned to Chennai after his historic victory against Ding Liren in Singapore, becoming the youngest World Champion ever.
title: Chennai comes to standstill as D Gukesh participates in ceremonial parade

description: Union Minister Amit Shah addressed the Rajya Sabha on the 75th anniversary of India's Constitution. He highlighted that both the BJP and Congress amended the Constitution during their respective reigns, with BJP making 22 amendments in 16 years and Congress making 77 in 55 years.
title: '54-yr-old who calls himself yuva': Shah's dig at Rahul in RS

description: Canadian Deputy PM Chrystia Freeland's shocking resignation throws Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's government into turmoil amidst economic woes and US trade threats. Freeland's scathing criticism of Trudeau's fiscal policies, coupled with looming tariffs from the US, leaves Canada vulnerable. Trudeau's weakening grip on power, reflected in declining poll numbers and cabinet exits, raises questions about his political future.
title: Will 'governor' Trudeau become first victim of Trump's tariff war?

description: Elon Musk's The Boring Company has proposed a $20 billion transatlantic tunnel connecting New York and London, utilizing Hyperloop technology to achieve travel times of under an hour.  This ambitious project faces significant technical, financial, and environmental challenges, but Musk believes advancements in tunneling technology make it feasible.  Experts remain skeptical, citing the project's scale and unproven technology.
title: New York to London in 1 hour? Elon Musk proposes $20 billion tunnel plan

description: The NBA Emirates Cup final is set. The Thunder will clash with the Bucks on December 15, 2024, at 7:00 pm ET. The game will occur at the Frost Bank Center in San Antonio. Giannis and the Bucks are favored. Catch the action on fuboTV, NBA League Pass, FanDuel Sports Network - Southwest, or FDSNNOX.
title: Oklahoma City Thunder vs Milwaukee Bucks game preview: How to watch, and more

description: Sindeep Singh, 48, has been sentenced to life in prison, with a minimum term of 31 years, for the brutal murder of his 76-year-old mother, Bhajan Kaur, in Leicester. Singh killed his mother following a family dispute over inheritance and attempted to conceal the crime by purchasing a sack barrow and spade, intending to bury her body in the garden.
title: Indian-origin man sent to life in jail for killing mother

description: Prithvi Shaw's omission from Mumbai's Vijay Hazare Trophy squad sparked a social media outburst from the young opener. Shaw highlighted his impressive List A stats—3,399 runs at an average of 55.7—questioning the decision. This follows his exclusion from the Ranji team and going unsold in the IPL.
title: 'What more do I have to see': Frustrated Prithvi Shaw reacts

description: Jasprit Bumrah, India's pace spearhead, showcased his batting prowess during the third Test in Brisbane.  Facing a follow-on threat, Bumrah's resilient 10* helped India avert it.  His 39-run partnership with Akash Deep for the 10th wicket proved crucial, highlighting Bumrah's ability to contribute with the bat in crunch situations.
title: Bumrah 'the batter' walks the talk after his batting skills doubted

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy accused Russian troops of burning the faces of deceased North Korean soldiers to hide their presence in Ukraine.  Zelenskyy shared a video depicting the alleged act, condemning Russia's disrespect and cynical attempts to conceal North Korean involvement in the war. He called for an end to the conflict and accountability for Russia's actions.
title: Russians burning faces of dead North Korean soldiers, says Ukraine

description: The police is planning to challenge Allu Arjun's interim bail and go to the Supreme Court. The actor was arrested on Friday and released on Saturday morning after he spent a night in Jail.
title: Telangana Police to challenge Allu Arjun's bail in SC in stampede case: Report

description: Conor McGregor is set to return to combat sports, not in the UFC, but in a boxing exhibition match against Logan Paul in India, backed by the Ambani family. This marks McGregor's first fight since his losses to Dustin Poirier in 2021 and his second boxing venture after the Mayweather bout.
title: McGregor inks preliminary deal with Ambanis for showdown in India

description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella admitted Google earns more from Windows than Microsoft due to Chrome's browser dominance.  He views this as a chance to "relitigate" and regain market share, leveraging AI and new search technologies. Nadella also revealed his decade-long pursuit of an Apple search deal, ultimately won by OpenAI.
title: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella: Google makes more money on Windows than all of Microsoft

description: Noida Authority CEO Lokesh M disciplined staff by making them stand for 30 minutes after an elderly man was left waiting.  A viral video shows the employees standing at their desks.  This action followed the CEO witnessing the elderly man's prolonged wait, prompting praise online for addressing negligence and improving customer service.
title: Watch: Noida official punishes govt staff for neglecting elderly couple

description: A Sambhal temple reopened after 46 years of abandonment.  The temple was closed due to the 1978 riots.  Many Hindu families fled the area during that time.  The district administration renamed the temple Sambhaleshwar Mahadev.  Idols of other deities were discovered in a well.  The temple will be restored.
title: '25-30 Hindu families lived in Sambhal temple area, left after 1978 riots'

description: Singer-actor Diljit Dosanjh sparked controversy over his spelling of "Punjab" as "PANJAB" in a social media post, attributing it to a conspiracy. He defended his choice, emphasizing the word's meaning and criticizing the use of English for such theories. Guru Randhawa's subsequent posts urging unity and patriotism fueled speculation of a connection to the controversy.
title: Diljit Dosanjh on why he wrote ‘Punjab as PANJAB; Guru Randhawa shares posts

description: A Bengaluru tech professional, Mahesh Suthar, exposed a taxi scam at the airport involving a fake Uber app called "Blumeter." The driver inflated the fare by Rs 1,000, attributing it to GST, and refused a physical bill. Suthar shared his experience online, warning others about the deceptive practice of manipulating fares through the app.
title: Man faces Uber 'fake fare screen' scam; shares these tips on how not to be fooled

description: Union Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan announced that from 2025, the NTA will stop conducting recruitment exams and focus solely on higher education entrance tests. Reforms follow controversies like NEET UG leaks and UGC NET irregularities. A government panel, led by Dr. K. Radhakrishnan, recommended restructuring NTA to improve exam security, accountability, and operational efficiency.
title: Edu min announces NTA overhaul with recruitment exams ending by 2025

description: India averted the follow-on in the Brisbane Test against Australia, thanks to a gritty last-wicket stand between Akash Deep and Jasprit Bumrah. Deep's unbeaten 27, including a six off Cummins, pushed India past the follow-on target. Australia's victory hopes dimmed further with a calf injury ruling out Josh Hazlewood for the rest of the series.
title: Kohli’s bat works wonders for Akash Deep as India avert follow-on

description: India's lower order staged a thrilling fightback against Australia at the Gabba, narrowly avoiding the follow-on on another rain-affected day. Jasprit Bumrah and debutant Akash Deep's unbeaten 39-run partnership, punctuated by a six each, proved crucial. Akash Deep's 27* turned out to be the second-highest score by an Indian No. 11 in Australia.
title: 3rd Test: India's tail wags defiantly to avoid follow-on

description: Law Minister Arjun Meghwal introduced 'one nation, one election' bills, facing strong opposition.  The bills failed to secure the required two-thirds majority. Opposition parties criticized the move as an attack on federalism, while the government defended it as constitutional.  Home Minister Amit Shah revealed PM Modi's suggestion to send the bill to a Joint Parliamentary Committee for further review.
title: 'ONOE' bill tabled in Lok Sabha; oppn calls it 'anti- Constitutional'

description: India's National Testing Agency (NTA) conducted a record low of 29 exams in 2024, a significant drop from 66 in 2023. This decline follows a year plagued by paper leaks, postponements, and administrative issues, impacting 85.78 lakh registered students. The NTA, responsible for major exams like NEET, JEE, and CUET, faced criticism and leadership changes.
title: NTA exam count hits record low: Govt data reveals 50% drop

description: The government's PAN 2.0 project introduces enhanced PAN cards with improved security features. However, scammers are exploiting the rollout by tricking individuals into paying for unnecessarily for new cards.
title: PAN 2.0: Beware of new scam! Here’s what you shouldknow

description: China has denied allegations that businessman Yang Tengbo used his ties with Britain's Prince Andrew for espionage. Yang, banned from the UK, insists he's done nothing unlawful and is a victim of changing political climates. Prince Andrew confirmed he cut contact with Yang after security concerns arose, stating no sensitive information was exchanged.
title: China dismisses spying allegations involving Prince Andrew, 'spy H6'

description: India narrowly averted the follow-on in the third Test against Australia in Brisbane, thanks to a crucial last-wicket partnership between Jasprit Bumrah and Akash Deep. In reply to Australia's 445 runs, India reached 252/9 at stumps on Day 4, with Akash (27*) and Bumrah (10*) adding an unbeaten 39 runs for the 10th wicket.
title: Explained: How follow-on rule works in Test cricket

description: KL Rahul received a massive lifeline early on Day 4 at the Gabba when Steve Smith dropped a straightforward catch off Pat Cummins. Rahul, then on 33, capitalized on this reprieve, reaching his 17th Test fifty. Commentator Brad Haddin criticized Smith's lapse in concentration. Rahul played with assurance, judiciously leaving deliveries and defending solidly.
title: 'Dropped an absolute soda': Steve Smith drops a sitter. Watch

description: Pat Cummins' superb spell dismantled Rohit Sharma's innings in Brisbane, extending the Indian captain's struggles in Australia.  Sharma's loose push at a good-length delivery led to his dismissal, highlighting a lack of confidence and the weight of past failures.  Despite Australia being a bowler down, Sharma couldn't capitalize, adding to his string of disappointing performances.
title: Like Virat Kohli, Rohit Sharma, too, a master of his own demise

description: Veteran Tollywood actor Mohan Babu is embroiled in a series of controversies, including assault allegations and a family feud with his son, Manchu Manoj. Following an altercation at his residence where a journalist was allegedly injured, Rachakonda police issued a notice to Mohan Babu, demanding his cooperation. Commissioner Sudheer Babu warned of potential arrest if the actor fails to comply after December 24th, a deadline granted by the court. Three separate cases have been filed related to the family dispute and the alleged assault.
title: Mohan Babu faces legal heat: Police threaten arrest over assault case
Bahrain-bound AI express flight returns to Cochin airport after tyre trouble

description: Ravindra Jadeja's resilient 77 and KL Rahul's determined 84 played a key role as India saved themselves the embarrassment of following-on against Australia at the Gabba.  Jasprit Bumrah and Akash Deep took India past the 245-run mark, in response to Australia's 445 runs. India finished the day at 252/9 with the seamers taking India to safety.
title: When was the last time India were forced to follow-on?

description: India pulled off a dramatic escape on Day 4 of the third Test against Australia at the Gabba, narrowly avoiding the follow-on. A spirited last-wicket stand of 39 runs between Akash Deep (27*) and Jasprit Bumrah (10*) propelled India past the follow-on target of 246, ending the day at 252/9.
title: Virat, Rohit celebrate in style as India save follow-on - WATCH

description: Rumford, Maine, residents encountered brown snow last Tuesday due to a paper mill mishap. Spent black liquor, a paper production byproduct, was released, altering the snow's color and raising health concerns. Although non-poisonous, the snow's high pH prompted warnings against contact. The mill funded further tests, and officials reassured the public about minimal risks.
title: What caused brown snow in Maine, prompting warnings to 'avoid direct contact'?

description: The first Vande Bharat sleeper train prototype has been dispatched for field trials after undergoing quality checks.  Manufactured by BEML and ICF, it boasts a 160 kmph top speed, enhanced safety features, and improved passenger comfort, aiming to surpass Rajdhani Express.
title: Vande Bharat sleeper a step closer tolaunch

description: The opposition parties have rejected the 'One Nation, One Election' bill, set to be tabled in the Lok Sabha. Congress, SP, and Shiv Sena (UBT) criticized the bill as unconstitutional, undemocratic, and an attempt to centralize power.
title: 'Move towards dictatorship': Opposition slams 'one nation, one election' Bill

description: Jensen Huang's wealth grew significantly in 2024.  Nvidia's success in the AI sector fueled this growth.  His net worth reached over $45 billion.  This put him behind Elon Musk and Mark Zuckerberg in wealth gains.  Nvidia's stock soared by 177%. Huang owns about 3.5% of the company.  Musk and Zuckerberg also saw massive increases in their wealth.
title: Nvidia CEO ranks 3rd in 2024 wealth gains; trails behind Musk, Zuckerberg

description: A blast-like noise occurred at Islamabad Police Station in Amritsar, Punjab, around 3 am on Tuesday.  Ten individuals from an organized module were arrested after claiming responsibility on social media.  Police detained two brothers, one a juvenile, and are pursuing Aman Khokhar and others. No damage or injuries were reported.
title: 'Blast' at Amritsar's Islamabad police station sends cops into a tizzy

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali criticizes young Indian batters Shubman Gill and Yashasvi Jaiswal for their dismissals in the Brisbane Test, emphasizing their need for greater hunger for runs. He contrasts their approach with established players like Kohli and Rohit, highlighting the youngsters' need to learn from legends like Sunil Gavaskar.
title: 'Shubman Gill ko runs ki bilkul bhookh nahi hai'

description: A high-ranking Russian military commander, Igor Kirillov, and his second-in-command were killed in Moscow on Tuesday.  A bomb concealed in a scooter detonated outside a residential building on Ryazansky Prospekt, claiming their lives.  The explosion occurred approximately 4.35 miles southeast of the Kremlin.  Russian authorities are investigating the incident.
title: Top Russian general in charge of nuclear protection forces killed in Moscow blast

description: Two people operating an unlicensed tattoo parlor in Trichy were arrested by police. The duo advertised extreme body modifications like tongue splitting and eyeball tattooing on social media. Authorities discovered surgical equipment during an inspection and sealed the shop due to public health risks. The owner, who reportedly received eyeball tattooing in Mumbai, lacked proper training.
title: ‘Tongue slitting’ ad on Trichy tattoo shop lands two in jail
After Palestine row, Priyanka carries 'stand with Bangladesh minorities' bag

description: Rohit Sharma's struggles continued in the Brisbane Test, falling for just 10 runs, and his brief stay included a mix-up with KL Rahul. Rahul (84) and Ravindra Jadeja then built a crucial partnership. Rain interrupted play with India at 180/6, still trailing by 265 runs. The five-Test series stands at 1-1.
title: 'Mai ruk gaya tha yaar': Rohit tells Rahul after mix-up

description: The record-breaking success of "Pushpa 2: The Rule" continues as its OTT release on Netflix is anticipated.  The streaming giant reportedly acquired the rights for a staggering Rs 275 crore. Fans can expect the film to be available around February 2025 in multiple languages, following its theatrical run which saw it become the 3rd biggest Indian grosser.
title: Pushpa 2 OTT release: Where to watch

description: KL Rahul's impressive Test average in SENA countries since 2020 has surpassed Indian stalwarts Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma.  Despite pressure, Rahul's composed batting, including a crucial 84-run knock against Australia, highlights his reliability while Kohli and Rohit struggle with form in the 2024-25 season.
title: Rahul better than Virat, Rohit, Pant in SENA countries since 2020

description: A 15-year-old girl opened fire at Abundant Life Christian School in Madison, Wisconsin, killing a teacher and a student before taking her own life. The attack occurred during a study hall, and a second-grade student called 911. Six others were injured, two critically. Police are investigating a possible motive and the origin of the handgun used.
title: Who was Natalie Rupnow? 15-year-old Madison school shooter
Meet Indian-American chef Priyanka Naik: From tech layoff to 6-figure culinary star

description: Federal agencies addressed recent drone sighting concerns, clarifying most were legitimate or misidentified objects.  Thousands of drones operate legally daily, and while some sightings near military bases are under investigation, no national security threat is currently evident.  Authorities are using advanced technology to monitor the situation and assure public safety.
title: 'Some are stars mistaken as drones': US Homeland Security on mysterious sightings

description: Virat Kohli had an intense net session in Brisbane.  He faced deliveries from various bowlers.  Kohli concentrated on his drives and leaving deliveries outside off-stump.  Coaches observed and assisted him.  The practice aimed to improve his form after recent low scores.  Kohli wants to perform well in the remaining matches.
title: Day after another sordid show, Kohli works to fix flaws in the nets

description: A former CIA officer suggests the recent surge in Northeast drone sightings could be a classified government exercise testing evasion or detection technology.  This theory contrasts with federal officials downplaying the incidents, despite receiving thousands of tips.  The lack of transparency fuels public concern and speculation about the drones' true purpose.
title: Drone mystery 'extremely unsettling': Ex-CIA officer reveals chilling theory

description: Canadian deputy PM Chrystia Freeland resigned abruptly, citing policy disagreements with Prime Minister Justin Trudeau over handling US tariff threats. Freeland, also the finance minister, stressed the need for fiscal prudence against potential trade wars, seemingly criticizing Trudeau's recent tax policies. Her departure, hours before a scheduled financial update, raises questions about Trudeau's leadership and the nation's economic direction.
title: Why Canada's deputy PM Chrystia Freeland stepped down

description: KL Rahul's composed batting technique has stood out against Australia's bowling attack in the Border Gavaskar Trophy. While other Indian batsmen edged deliveries outside off-stump, Rahul played closer to his body, letting the ball come to him. This contrasts with Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli, whose forward lunges resulted in dismissals.
title: Where Rahul has out-techniqued Virat and Rohit

description: A 15-year-old student opened fire at Abundant Life Christian School in Madison, Wisconsin, killing a teacher and a fellow student before taking her own life. Six others were injured.  Police responded swiftly, and the community is reeling from the tragedy just days before Christmas break. This marks the 322nd school shooting in the US this year.
title: 'When they heard lockdown ... ': How Wisconsin school shooting unfolded

description: Former Pakistani minister Chaudhry Fawad Hussain praised Congress MP Priyanka Gandhi for carrying a "Palestine" bag to Parliament, drawing criticism from the BJP, who accused her of "appeasement."  Gandhi defended her action, stating it was her choice of attire and rejecting the BJP's patriarchal critique. This follows Gandhi's recent display of solidarity with Palestine by wearing a keffiyeh.
title: 'Stood tall amidst pigmies': Ex-Pak minister lauds Priyanka for Palestine bag

description: President-elect Trump criticized President Biden's decision to allow Ukraine to use US long-range missiles against Russia, calling it "stupid" and a "big mistake." Trump stated his administration wasn't consulted and suggested he might reverse the decision. The White House defended the move, explaining it followed extensive deliberations.
title: 'Very stupid': Trump slams Biden for allowing Ukraine to use ATACMS against Russia

description: Australia's Information Commissioner dropped its lawsuit against Meta after a $31.85 million settlement. The case stemmed from the Cambridge Analytica scandal, where Facebook was accused of exposing user data via the "This Is Your Digital Life" quiz app. The original lawsuit, filed in 2020, alleged that Facebook improperly disclosed the personal information of Australian users.
title: Meta to pay $31.85m in privacy settlement with Australian regulator
Drone mystery: 'Lawful, legal,' White House responds to speculation

description: A Chinese businessman, Yang Tengbo, with ties to Prince Andrew, denies UK espionage allegations.  The Home Office accuses Yang of working for China's United Front Work Department, posing a national security threat.  Yang, banned from the UK, insists he is innocent.  Prince Andrew confirms past contact but ceased it after concerns arose.
title: Prince Andrew's alleged connection with Chinese 'spy H6': Explained

description: Citi downgraded TCS, Tech Mahindra, and LTIMindtree, citing weak demand. Jefferies lowered PI Industries' target price but maintained a 'buy' rating. Goldman Sachs recommended buying Aurobindo Pharma, foreseeing biosimilar monetization and new growth avenues. Elara Securities upgraded BEML to 'reduce'. Axis Securities highlighted high-dividend-yield stocks, including Vedanta, Coal India, and Hindustan Zinc.
title: Buy or sell: Stocks on brokerages’ radar for today

description: India opener KL Rahul's impressive knock of 84 ended with a stunning catch by Steve Smith on day four of the Brisbane Test at the Gabba, after Smith had dropped him earlier in the day at the score of 33. Rahul and Jadeja built a crucial 67-run partnership, rescuing India from a precarious 74/5.
title: Smith's blinder denies Rahul a century in Gabba - Watch

description: Delhi-NCR has implemented GRAP-IV restrictions due to severe air quality, crossing into the 'severe' zone.  Schools will adopt hybrid learning, construction and demolition activities are banned, and vehicle restrictions are in place.  This is the second time GRAP-IV has been enforced this winter, following revised guidelines.
title: Delhi air ‘severe’: GRAP-4 curbs reimposed; what's allowed and what's not

description: A member of PM's Museum & Library has urged Rahul Gandhi to return letters written by Nehru to Lady Mountbatten, JP and others, which were allegedly withdrawn at Sonia Gandhi's orders, prompting BJP to ask what the family is hiding.
title: BJP: What's in Nehru letters that Gandhis want to hide?
Trudeau to resign? High odds on Canada PM’s exit before April

description: Dominic LeBlanc has been appointed as Canada's new finance minister following Chrystia Freeland's abrupt resignation.  Freeland's departure stems from disagreements with Prime Minister Trudeau over fiscal policy. LeBlanc, a close Trudeau ally, faces the challenge of managing a growing deficit and potential US tariffs.  His appointment aims to stabilize the government amidst economic uncertainty and rising political pressure.
title: Who is Dominic LeBlanc? Trudeau's replacement for Freeland as Canada's FM

description: Pushpa: The Rule, starring Allu Arjun and Rashmika Mandanna, rakes in Rs 929.85 crore despite a dip in second Monday collections. The film's second weekend saw a surge, crossing Rs 725.8  crore in its first week.  The controversy surrounding Allu Arjun's arrest after a fan's death allegedly boosted collections. Trade analysts predict the film may soon hit Rs 1,000 crore mark at the domestic box office.
title: 'Pushpa 2' box office collection: Allu Arjun starrer records its lowest Monday

description: A 17-year-old student opened fire at Abundant Life Christian School in Madison, Wisconsin, killing a teacher and a fellow student before taking her own life. The shooting occurred just days before Christmas break, leaving the community devastated. President Biden condemned the incident and renewed calls for stricter gun control.
title: Madison school shooting: 'Female student' kills two before taking her own life

description: The Allahabad High Court granted transit anticipatory bail to Sushil Singhania, uncle of Atul Subhash's widow, in an abetment to suicide case. Subhash, a Bengaluru techie, left a note blaming his wife's harassment. Singhania's lawyer questioned the note's authenticity and highlighted the family court judge's involvement.
title: Bengaluru techie suicide: Estranged wife's uncle Sushil gets bail

description: In Lucknow, a 26-year-old man, Dharmesh Rawat, and his 24-year-old girlfriend, Sangeeta, were arrested for the murder of Dharmesh's father, Ramu Rawat.  Dharmesh, motivated by a property dispute, pushed his father into a borewell and set him on fire. The incident occurred on the family's farmland after Ramu refused to transfer the property to his son and Sangeeta.
title: UP: Man burns father alive with girlfriend's help over property dispute

description: A 15-year-old boy in Bahraich, India, died after falling into a harvester. Two men, Sanjay Verma and Lavkush, dismembered his body with the harvester and buried the parts to conceal the crime.  Police discovered the remains and arrested the accused, who confessed.  The case is being fast-tracked for maximum punishment.
title: Missing teen’s body found chopped into 17 pieces, buried separately

description: Zerodha CEO Nithin Kamath highlighted the double-edged nature of regulations, citing P2P lending as an example.  Recent RBI guidelines requiring faster fund settlements have forced P2P platforms to revamp their business models, impacting their ability to hold funds and facilitate lending.
title: Zerodha CEO Nithin Kamath calls regulations ‘double-edged sword’

description: State Bank of India (SBI) has issued a warning to its customers about deepfake videos circulating on social media. These videos falsely feature SBI's top management promoting fraudulent investment schemes with unrealistic returns. SBI clarifies it has no association with such schemes and urges the public to remain vigilant against these scams.
title: SBI releases public caution notice: We clarify that ...

description: Dinga Dinga continues to baffle health professionals as investigations are underway. While its symptoms can be distressing. The Ugandan health system, with support from local and international organizations, is actively working to uncover the origins of this mysterious illness and find lasting solutions.
title: What is Dinga Dinga, the ‘excessive body shaking’ that is in news?

description: Zomato's global head of finance, Hemal Jain, resigned after six years with the company.  Her departure follows a recent Rs 803 crore GST demand notice against Zomato.  This marks the second senior management exit in recent months, following co-founder Akriti Chopra's resignation in September.
title: Zomato global head of finance steps down; "After much...," wrote Jain
